==English==
===Etymology===
[[petrol]] + [[-head]]

===Noun===
'''petrolhead''' (''plural'' '''petrolheads''')

#(''figurative'') A person who is very [[reliant]] on and fond of using his or her [[car]] and objects to any attempts to dissuade him or her to use alternative [[means of transport]].
#(''Australian, New Zealand'') A member of a wider class of people often known as [[bogan]]s. A petrolhead lives for his car and enjoys showing it off and making a lot of noise with it. A petrolhead can often be identified by his clothing and general lifestyle.